/target
**/*.rs.bk
.DS_Store
*.snap.new
# `.prova/` is SOURCE, not build output: it holds this project's manifest, its runtime companion,
# and its local plugins. It was ignored wholesale when it existed only to hold generated LuaLS
# annotations — which prova no longer writes into a project at all (they live in the cache now).
# Ignoring it hid the manifest, so the proof suite could not run from a fresh clone.
# Only genuinely generated artifacts are ignored. (This repo's own /.luarc.json is COMMITTED and
# points at library/ — the hand-written source stubs — because prova is where they come from.)
/.prova/annotations/
# Generated LuaLS IDE artifacts from running the example suites. prova writes .luarc.json into each
# example's project root; it holds machine-local absolute paths, so it is per-machine, not shared.
examples/**/.luarc.json
# Held-topology run-state from `prova up`/`start` in the examples (self-ignores too).
examples/**/running/
.last-failed.json
